The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House, regarding the issuance of an Executive Order addressing the threat posed by certain connected software applications. The Executive Order is aimed at software applications designed, developed, manufactured, or supplied by persons owned by, controlled by, or subject to the jurisdiction or direction of a foreign adversary, including the People's Republic of China. The President states that additional consideration needs to be given to the national emergency declared in a previous Executive Order, which focuses on securing the information and communications technology and services supply chain. The letter includes a copy of the Executive Order that has been issued.